HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 538
By Hale
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Walter Glenn Birdwell,
Jr., of Carthage.
WHEREAS, it was with great sadness that we learned of the passing of Walter Glenn
Birdwell, Jr., a longtime banker who gave back to his Carthage community in numerous ways;
and
WHEREAS, Mr. Birdwell was a graduate of Vanderbilt University, where he was a
member of the Sigma Chi Fraternity and a member of the wrestling team during his varsity days;
and
WHEREAS, most importantly, he met his future wife, Helen Walton, there, and it was at
Vanderbilt they began their wonderful life together; and
WHEREAS, after graduation, Mr. Birdwell served his country in the United States Army
during the Korean War; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Birdwell worked for seventy years at Citizens Bank of Carthage, which
was founded by his father and local investors; the bank opened on October 26, 1929, three
days before the stock market crash on Black Tuesday; and
WHEREAS, Walter Glenn Birdwell served with distinction as chairman of the board of
Citizens Bank of Carthage from 1988 until his passing; a mere month before his death at the
age of ninety-six, he still attended the bank's 7:30 a.m. meeting every day; and
WHEREAS, a giant in the industry, Mr. Birdwell was a board member of the Tennessee
Bankers Association (TBA), was a founder and the first president of the TBA Young Bankers,
and served as president of the TBA Independent Bankers Division; and
