WHEREAS, he served the larger community as chairman of the Smith County Industrial
Board, president of the Smith County Chamber of Commerce, and president of the Lions Club
and as a member of the Smith County Help Center and Smith County Historical Society; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Birdwell expressed his faith at Carthage United Methodist Church,
where he served in many leadership roles; and
WHEREAS, Walter Glenn Birdwell loved traveling the world with Helen, his beloved wife
of seventy-two years; he was also an avid outdoorsman and loved duck hunting, snow skiing,
and watersports; and
WHEREAS, he will be deeply mourned but fondly remembered by his loving family,
including his wife; his children, Sue (Jerry) Ishee, Walter Glenn "Birdy" (Christie) Birdwell III, and
Ann (Matt) Dobson; and his grandsons, Matthew H. Dobson VI and Walter Birdwell Dobson; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Birdwell was preceded in death by his parents, Catherine Hargis
Birdwell and Walter Glenn Birdwell, Sr; and
WHEREAS, Walter Glenn Birdwell was an outstanding professional, a devoted family
man, and a pillar of his community, and his passing creates a void that will not be easily filled;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Walter Glenn Birdwell, Jr., of Carthage, reflecting
fondly upon his life of purpose and commitment to others.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and extend our
condolences to Mr. Birdwell's family and many friends.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
